Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The figures given in this report are significantly lower than the numbers of fatalities and total cases cited in the 1st report [1] above. Given the sharp increase in the number of reported cases in the past 2-3 days, it is difficult to understand that the outbreak is under control and decreasing as the health officials indicated. Spraying is, at best, a temporary measure to reduce vector mosquito populations. Although adult mosquitoes may be killed, if the breeding sites remain, a new crop of adults will emerge quickly and YF virus transmission will continue. If the vaccination campaign can start on Tuesday, rather than at the end of the week as indicated in [1] above, that will be very helpful in reducing the number of cases. - Mod.TY]
